I've lived in Chicago since 2002 and Theory is my favorite bar in the city. Joel and his staff are genuine, hard-working people that provide top notch service and a high quality product. Whether you're looking to have a beer at the bar alone or eat dinner with friends/family, you will enjoy your experience at Theory. Cheers!

Theory is one of the finest establishments in River North. The food is amazing and the drinks are exceptional. The staff is very professional and the ownership (who will likely stop by your table) is outstanding. They care very much about their patrons and always extend their appreciation for supporting them.  Theory is a locally owned establishment and it shows. Be sure to stop by for some unbelievable pretzels and queso.

We went here today for brunch and I can confidently say this one was one of the best brunch experiences I’ve had in a while. The Bloody Mary and “Martini’s Mule” were delicious, and the omelette was absolutely amazing. I got it with bacon, mushrooms, and cheddar cheese and it was soft, fluffy, and incredibly flavorful. The best part is that the owner, Joel, is an incredible host and extremely welcoming. He made sure we were taken care of the entire way and his team was attentive and friendly. If you’re looking for a sports bar with good vibes, great food, and delicious drinks you need to come check it out! Definitely not your average sports bar!

Met up with our granddaughter and her boyfriend here before heading to Lookingglass Theatre for 20,000 Leagues. Chose Theory because it was an easy walk from the theatre and offered a great discount if you had theater tickets.  On the plus side: great atmosphere, friendly and helpful staff, efficient service (we mentioned we were going to the theatre when we made reservations and they made sure we had plenty of time to get there), surprisingly affordable prices.  On the minus side - and the ONLY reason for less than 5 stars - my wife and I both ordered a half order of the biscuits and gravy and agreed that it was the worst we've ever had. There was more than enough to be sure, but the biscuits were hard and stale and both the look and taste of the gravy were like nothing we've ever encountered...and that's NOT a compliment. Our granddaughter had the fried chicken sandwich and loved it, however. Takeaway is that Theory is a 5 star experience in every way...as long as you steer clear of the biscuits and gravy! UPDATE: I received a nice letter from Joel Sorinsky, owner of Theory, today with his sincere apology for our unfortunate dining experience - and a gift card so we can give it another chance.  Would that every business were this responsive to their customers.  I am sorely tempted to bump my review up to 5 stars...but the biscuits and gravy really was awful.  Joel's unexpected response certainly deserves to raise the review to 4 stars, though.  Thank you, Joel - and you can count on seeing us next time we're in our favorite city.  We might even bring along a really good recipe for biscuits and gravy!

She only honored the discounts bc we refused to believe her && another server walked by &&& over heard.  Her, 'Ohh we just got new menus &&& they changed things since I got back from vacation. But yeah that's totally happy hour it just doesn't say.' My friend, 'Well it looks like drink specials also changed && you just admitted you haven't been here.' Other server, 'Well I have been here && those are now our daily specials.'  Long story short we never received an apology bc we weren't willing to pay full price && sponsor her next vacation.

Spent a week in Chicago on business back in October. Randomly found this place, and it became my go-to every night. Great door guys, very helpful, and the owner was very present- my friend and I noticed a group lacking seating so we moved down one stool each to allow them to all sit together. The owner happened to notice this and brought us shots to thank us for being nice. It was unexpected but a very decent gesture by him. Food was good and beer prices were good too. If we ever got bored anywhere we had a running theme- let’s go back to Theory. We never regretted it.

I went here for a charity event. The layout of the place was pretty average, bar in the center and tables all around the walls. Lots of TVs and rather dark. I guess this would be for the high end sports fan.  The food was good, for bar food. Jz is vegetarian and so she grabbed the hummus and pita and some salad things. The hummus was decent, but it probably came out of a box. Yes, I can tell the difference. The sliders and the tuna were good, the sliders particularly. There was also an awesome chicken with blue cheese slider/ sandwich that I couldn't get enough of, and sadly I had just one.  The drinks were ok, nothing great. I would say, for the price I would expect better bar food but I think the prices are for the location, rather than the food. Good place to meet dad-in-law when you wanna do drinks.

Very Good Lunch Spot. I came here with no expectations since I had never really heard much about the place. I had the pesto panini and tater tots. The chicken on the panini was cooked perfectly, and the pesto was delicious. The tots were good but nothing special. I'll have to try this place again.

Overall: Great spot for a typical sports bar option for general food and drinks or game day. It knows the audience and caters to it well.  The good: Went during lunch with some coworkers and the experience was great. They take online reservations which was clutch and the service was fast and friendly throughout. No slipups whatsoever. The food is your standard bar fare, but it was all great and the portion sizes are good. The prices are downtown-based, but that was expected. Plenty of TVs all around. The kale caesar I had was plentiful and tasty.  The not-so-good: They were playing their top-40 chart music too loud. It was hard to have a conversation at times. Again, we were there for lunch, so I'm sure it's different at night or during game days.  Atmosphere: 8/10 Service: 9/10 Food: 8/10
